{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866671550,"sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","part":{"id":"prt_d79e6d897001GuG0peL6Efh3Pr","messageID":"msg_d79e6c2080013qhwwcCTCH4g4t","sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-013  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Redis Storage Implementation provides a concrete implementation of the Store interface using Redis as the backend. It handles connection management, command execution, and Redis-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: (TBD - Requirements to be defined based on AR-012 interface contract)\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## Changes to Base Specification\n22: \n23: No modifications to existing interfaces. This AR implements the Store interface defined in AR-012 for Redis backend.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## New Interfaces\n28: \n29: (TBD - Implementation-specific types and functions)\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## Modified Interfaces\n34: \n35: None. This AR implements existing interfaces without modification.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## Behavioral Changes\n40: \n41: | Behavior | Before | After |\n42: |----------|--------|-------|\n43: | Redis Store | Interface only | Full Redis implementation |\n44: | Connection management | None | Redis client with pooling |\n45: | Command execution | None | Full Redis command support |\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n52: |------------|---------|---------|\n53: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client for Go |\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Store interface definition |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo type definition |\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## File Index\n60: \n61: | Path | Purpose |\n62: |------|---------|\n63: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis Store implementation |\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## Constants\n68: \n69: (TBD)\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## Environment Variables\n74: \n75: (TBD - Redis-specific configuration)\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## API Endpoints Summary\n80: \n81: This AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Migration Notes\n86: \n87: - **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` to go.mod\n88: - **Environment setup**: Configure `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n93: \n94: 1. **Implementation Completeness**: All Store interface methods implemented\n95: 2. **Error Handling**: Redis errors properly translated to store errors\n96: 3. **Atomicity**: Pipeline operations ensure atomic writes\n97: 4. **Index Management**: ZSET indexes maintained correctly\n98: 5. **Connection Management**: Proper client lifecycle handling\n99: 6. **Test Coverage**: Unit and integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides a concrete implementation of the Store interface using Redis as the backend. It handles connection management, command execution, and Redis-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n(TBD - Requirements to be defined based on AR-012 interface contract)\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866671514,"end":1775866671548}}}}
