{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775866703868,"sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","part":{"id":"prt_d79e76ff7001jnzGVC3B26GJuz","messageID":"msg_d79e7226a001xfx34qL7EHLyoE","sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775866710502,"sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","part":{"id":"prt_d79e78691001w8PiYiHcdzdLcm","messageID":"msg_d79e7226a001xfx34qL7EHLyoE","sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding. The AR-013 delta-spec.md needs to be completed with proper GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios. Let me write the complete delta specification:","time":{"start":1775866710501,"end":1775866710501}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775866889163,"sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","part":{"id":"prt_d79e85663001lfwPoSMnW3Z8QV","messageID":"msg_d79e7226a001xfx34qL7EHLyoE","sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","type":"text","text":" existence","time":{"start":1775866889157,"end":1775866889157}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866889203,"sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","part":{"id":"prt_d79e789e7001NYQ8RRouN1iUAL","messageID":"msg_d79e7226a001xfx34qL7EHLyoE","sessionID":"ses_286197a78ffew2etUbcd1oyk8z","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides concrete implementations of the Store interface using Redis and Valkey as backends. It handles connection management, command execution, and backend-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Redis-backed Store implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` that satisfies the Store interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server at `REDIS_ADDR`\n- **AND** a valid `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command\n- **AND** require string response `PONG`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Ping fails on connection error\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable Redis server\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n- **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Redis\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `redis.Nil` error\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Redis\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates input\n- **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n  - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n- **AND** all commands SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n- **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL return `false`\n- **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** when result is `false`, return error `key not exists`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify expiry or activity ZSETs\n\n#### Scenario: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n  - `DEL session:sess-1`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes queries expiry ZSET\n- **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **AND** `limit = 10`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGE session:expiry -inf 1234567890 BYSCORE LIMIT 0 10`\n- **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n- **GIVEN** `limit = 0` (or negative)\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n\n#### Scenario: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes skips orphaned entries\n- **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains session ID `orphan-1`\n- **AND** key `session:orphan-1` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL skip `orphan-1` in results\n- **AND** return only valid sessions\n\n#### Scenario: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes queries activity ZSET\n- **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **AND** `limit = 10`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGE session:last_activity -inf 1234567890 BYSCORE LIMIT 0 10`\n- **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n- **GIVEN** `limit = -1` (or zero)\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Redis\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity verifies existence\n- **GIVEN** session ID `unknown-sess`\n- **AND** key `session:unknown-sess` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"unknown-sess\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `EXISTS session:unknown-sess`\n- **AND** when result is `0`, return `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT update activity index\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time for zero\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** `at = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** current time is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()`\n- **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567890 sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Close releases connection\n- **GIVEN** a `redisStore` instance with active connection\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `cli.Close()` on the Redis client\n- **AND** return the resulting error (nil on success)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n- **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command via `B().Ping().Build()`\n- **AND** require string response `PONG`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n- **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `IsValkeyNil` error\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n- **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses DoMulti\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute via `DoMulti`:\n  - `SET session:sess-1 {json} NX`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n- **AND** check first result for \"OK\" indicating success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n- **THEN** `SET NX` SHALL NOT return \"OK\"\n- **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** when result is not \"OK\", return error `key not exists`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n- **AND** SHALL NOT modify expiry or activity ZSETs\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses DoMulti\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute via `DoMulti`:\n  - `DEL session:sess-1`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes queries expiry ZSET\n- **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **AND** `limit = 10`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf 1234567890 LIMIT 0 10`\n- **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n- **GIVEN** `limit = 0` (or negative)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes skips orphaned entries\n- **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains session ID `orphan-1`\n- **AND** key `session:orphan-1` does NOT exist (MGET returns empty string)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL skip empty results\n- **AND** return only valid sessions\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes queries activity ZSET\n- **GIVEN** `before = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **AND** `limit = 10`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf 1234567890 LIMIT 0 10`\n- **AND** for each returned session ID, fetch the full document\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n- **GIVEN** `limit = -1` (or zero)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity verifies existence\n- **GIVEN** session ID `unknown-sess`\n- **AND** key `session:unknown-sess` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"unknown-sess\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `EXISTS session:unknown-sess`\n- **AND** when result is `0`, return `ErrNotFound`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT update activity index\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time for zero\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** `at = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** current time is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()`\n- **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567890 sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connection\n- **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connection\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `cli.Close()` on the Valkey client\n- **AND** return `nil`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis address is required\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** `newRedisStore()` is called\n- **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `REDIS_ADDR is required`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT create a Redis client\n\n#### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n- **WHEN** `newRedisStore()` is called\n- **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `REDIS_PASSWORD is required`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis password can be disabled\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** `newRedisStore()` is called\n- **THEN** the function SHALL succeed\n- **AND** create a Redis client with empty password\n\n#### Scenario: Redis password requirement is case-insensitive\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE` (uppercase)\n- **WHEN** parsing the option\n- **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as disabled\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey address is required\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR is required`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT create a Valkey client\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey parses comma-separated addresses\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey1:6379,valkey2:6379,valkey3:6379`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** `InitAddress` SHALL be `[\"valkey1:6379\", \"valkey2:6379\", \"valkey3:6379\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** the function SHALL return an error indicating `VALKEY_PASSWORD is required`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** the function SHALL succeed\n- **AND** create a Valkey client without password\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache when VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` SHALL be `true`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient when VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` SHALL be `true`\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nNo modifications to existing interfaces. This AR implements the Store interface defined in AR-012 for Redis and Valkey backends.\n\n---\n\n## New Interfaces\n\n### Redis Store Internal Types\n\n```go\n// redisOptions holds Redis connection configuration.\ntype redisOptions struct {\n    Addr     string\n    Password string\n}\n```\n\n### Valkey Store Internal Types\n\n```go\n// valkeyOptions holds Valkey connection configuration.\ntype valkeyOptions struct {\n    InitAddress       []string\n    Password          string\n    DisableCache      bool\n    ForceSingleClient bool\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Modified Interfaces\n\nNone. This AR implements existing interfaces without modification.\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n| Behavior | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Redis Store | Interface only | Full Redis implementation in `redis.go` |\n| Valkey Store | Interface only | Full Valkey implementation in `valkey.go` |\n| Connection management | None | Redis client with pooling via go-redis/v9 |\n| Connection management | None | Valkey client via valkey-go |\n| Command execution | None | Full Redis command support via Pipeline |\n| Command execution | None | Full Valkey command support via DoMulti |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client for Go |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Latest | Valkey client for Go |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Store interface definition |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo type definition |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/store/redis.go` | Redis Store implementation |\n| `pkg/store/valkey.go` | Valkey Store implementation |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Provider selection and initialization |\n\n---\n\n## Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Key prefix for session data |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry tracking |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity tracking |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n### Redis Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Redis authentication password |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n\n### Valkey Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated Valkey addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Valkey authentication password |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client cache |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` for single client mode |\n\n*Required unless the corresponding `_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `false`\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\nThis AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` and `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` to go.mod\n- **Environment setup**: Configure `REDIS_ADDR` or `VALKEY_ADDR` before deployment\n- **File naming**: Implementation files are `redis.go` and `valkey.go` (not `store_redis.go`/`store_valkey.go`)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. **Redis Implementation Completeness**: All Store interface methods implemented for Redis\n2. **Valkey Implementation Completeness**: All Store interface methods implemented for Valkey\n3. **Error Handling**: Redis/Valkey errors properly translated to store errors (ErrNotFound)\n4. **Atomicity**: Pipeline operations ensure atomic writes for StoreSandbox and Delete\n5. **Index Management**: ZSET indexes maintained correctly for both backends\n6. **Connection Management**: Proper client lifecycle handling for both Redis and Valkey\n7. **Environment Validation**: Required environment variables validated at initialization\n8. **Test Coverage**: Unit and integration tests pass for both implementations\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis.go\">\nERROR [279:6] declared and not used: i\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go\">\nERROR [144:34] cannot use data (variable of type []byte) as string value in argument to s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value\nERROR [191:57] cannot use data (variable of type []byte) as string value in argument to s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value\nERROR [249:34] zrangeResult.ToStringSlice undefined (type valkey.ValkeyResult has no field or method ToStringSlice)\nERROR [272:34] zrangeResult.ToStringSlice undefined (type valkey.ValkeyResult has no field or method ToStringSlice)\nERROR [299:29] mgetResult.ToStringSlice undefined (type valkey.ValkeyResult has no field or method ToStringSlice)\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":278,"character":5},"end":{"line":278,"character":6}},"severity":1,"code":"UnusedVar","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UnusedVar"},"source":"compiler","message":"declared and not used: i","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":143,"character":33},"end":{"line":143,"character":37}},"severity":1,"code":"IncompatibleAssign","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#IncompatibleAssign"},"source":"compiler","message":"cannot use data (variable of type []byte) as string value in argument to s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value"},{"range":{"start":{"line":190,"character":56